<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. COMMITMENT TO ISRAEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for publishing "No Peace for the Peacemakers" by Hillel Bardin, Op-Ed 
Page, Sept. 16. 
</P>
<P>
The original Zionist myth was "There are no Palestinians" period. Recently the 
Israeli government replaced the original with one that states: "There are no 
Palestinians who are willing to talk peace." 
</P>
<P>
Bardin's column went a long way to shatter this myth. He eloquently presented 
the case of only five Palestinians. Like them, there are thousands who have 
been jailed, expelled, or even killed by the Israelis. 
</P>
<P>
We not only have a moral stake in the peace between Israel and the 
Palestinians, we also have a huge financial stake. Our moral obligation is to 
make sure that our money is not used to silence the peacemakers. 
</P>
<P>
SAMI M. ODEH 
</P>
<P>
Orange 
</P>
</TEXT>
