<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN'S BONNER WINS WFC HONOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sherdrick Bonner, quarterback of the Cal State Northridge football team, has 
been selected offensive player of the week in the Western Football Conference 
after leading the Matadors to a come-from-behind win over Central (Okla.) State 
of the Lone Star Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Bonner, a junior, completed 17 of 34 passes for 227 yards and two touchdowns -- 
the final one of 17 yards to Anthony Harris with 11 seconds left -- as CSUN 
defeated the Bronchos, 31-28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
