<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ROYAL SWEEPS WESTLAKE IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Setter Michelle Pagan had 16 assists and six digs Tuesday as Royal High cruised 
by Westlake, 15-5, 15-5, 15-5, in a Marmonte League girls' volleyball match at 
Royal. 
</P>
<P>
Stephanie Champ had eight kills for Royal (4-0, 3-0 in league play) and 
teammate Jennifer Hamilton added 10 blocks. Westlake dropped to 1-2 in league 
play. 
</P>
<P>
In other girls' volleyball matches: 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks d. Channel Islands, 15-4, 15-1, 15-6 -- Amy Chellevold had 11 
kills and Aimee Stone added nine for the Lancers, ranked No. 1 in the Southern 
Section 4-A Division, in a Marmonte League match at Channel Islands. 
</P>
<P>
Jennifer Thorsen added three kills and had 14 service points, including 10 in a 
row, for Thousand Oaks (6-0, 2-0). Channel Islands is 0-3 in league play. 
</P>
<P>
La Reina d. Oak Park, 15-11, 15-0, 15-3 -- Carolyn Russo had nine kills and 
Heather Freeman added seven to lead La Reina in a Tri-Valley League match. 
</P>
<P>
Freeman and Sandi Reese combined for 17 blocks for La Reina (4-1, 2-0), ranked 
fourth in the Southern Section 2-A Division. 
</P>
<P>
Louisville d. Calabasas, 15-5, 15-8, 15-11 -- Louisville needed only 55 minutes 
to win the nonleague match at Louisville. Mary Hudson had a team-high eight 
kills for Louisville (4-1), ranked No. 2 in the 4-A Division. Calabasas is 
ranked seventh in the 3-A. 
</P>
<P>
Burroughs d. Marymount 15-3, 9-15, 15-8, 10-15, 15-13 -- Jennifer Wagner had 11 
kills and Kim Barnfather had eight for host Burroughs (6-0) in a nonleague 
match. 
</P>
<P>
Cleveland d. North Hollywood, 15-8, 15-3, 15-8 -- Monica Martin had three kills 
for the Cavaliers (3-0) in a nonleague match at Cleveland. 
</P>
<P>
WATER POLO 
</P>
<P>
Harvard 16, St. John Bosco 9 -- Hassan Yardimichi scored five goals to lead 
Harvard, ranked third in the Southern Section 3-A Division, in a Del Rey League 
match at Harvard. 
</P>
<P>
Crespi 13, Servite 4 -- Vince Greco had a game-high five goals and teammate 
Jean Michel added three as Crespi (5-3, 1-1) defeated host Servite in a Del Rey 
League match. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 3, Orange Coast 3 -- Eric Gunther scored two goals and Richy Rungaitis 
added another as Moorpark (2-1-1) rallied from a 3-1 halftime deficit in a 
nonconference match at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Pierce d. College of the Canyons, 15-5, 15-3, 15-3 -- Anna Suarez had 16 kills 
and seven service aces and Carina Sailer added six service aces to pace the 
Brahmas (5-0, 4-0) in a Western State Conference match at Canyons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
