<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Shauna Snow, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Roe vs. Wade," the TV movie about the events that culminated in the 1973 
Supreme Court decision that legalized abortion in this country, will be 
released on home video early next year. The NBC-produced movie, which won Emmys 
for outstanding special and for Holly Hunter's lead performance just last week, 
first aired on the network last May. Generally, television movies air twice on 
the network before moving on to home video, but since NBC produced this project 
in house, the network can earn extra revenue from home video sales while 
retaining the rights to broadcast it again. Shauna Snow 
</P>
</TEXT>
