</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Citing a lack of evidence, a Colombian judge dropped charges against two 
reputed leaders of the Medellin drug cartel accused in the assassination of 
Colombia's attorney general and a kidnaping, a leading Bogota newspaper 
reported. The two -- Pablo Escobar and Gonzalo Rodriguez Gacha -- are being 
sought by U.S. authorities. The judge's action in Colombia apparently would not 
prevent their extradition. Meanwhile, in Washington, the White House announced 
that Colombian President Virgilio Barco Vargas will meet with President Bush on 
Thursday on his way to New York to address the United Nations. 
</P>
