<P>
Kaz Deyna, a member of five San Diego Sockers championship teams between 1981 
and 1987, had a blood-alcohol level of .20%, twice the legal limit, when he 
crashed into a parked truck and was killed on Sept. 1, the San Diego County 
Coroner's Office said. 
</P>
<P>
Deyna, 41, had a history of drunk driving. He was convicted three times in San 
Diego Municipal Court of driving under the influence. 
