<TEXT>
<P>
Teen-age tennis star Jennifer Capriati can play in her first professional 
tournament before her 14th birthday under a rules change, the Women's 
International Professional Tennis Council announced. 
</P>
<P>
Capriati, 13, winner of the junior French and U.S. opens, will be eligible to 
play in the $300,000 Florida women's championships and the International 
Players Championships at Key Biscayne, Fla. 
</P>
