<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: HIKER RESCUED AFTER 15 HOURS ON LEDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 29-year-old Arcadia hiker who stumbled over a precipice and onto a ledge in 
the Eaton Canyon area of Angeles National Forest was discovered Tuesday morning 
after spending more than 15 hours on the ledge in nothing but a T-shirt and 
shorts, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Brice Boyd was rescued by the Altadena Search and Rescue Team about 9:30 a.m. 
after a woman hiker spotted him perched on the ledge, where he landed after 
stumbling over the edge of a precipice about 6 p.m. Monday, sheriff's deputies 
said. The woman ran about a mile to a phone to call for help. 
</P>
<P>
A Los Angeles County Fire Department helicopter flew Boyd to Verdugo Hills 
Hospital, where he was in stable condition with a fractured rib and internal 
injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies said the warm weather enabled Boyd to survive the night on the ledge 
in light clothing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
