<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Accounting Merger Talks Halted: Arthur Andersen &amp; Co. and Price Waterhouse 
&amp; Co. said they have ended merger talks that would have created the world's 
biggest accounting and consulting company. The discussions were discontinued 
because differences could not be resolved within a realistic period, the 
companies said in a joint statement. Other factors, including regulatory 
concerns, also helped to derail the talks. The Justice Department asked Price 
Waterhouse for information, including client lists, shortly after the merger 
talks were announced July 6, an official said. He noted that the Department 
requested the same data from Arthur Andersen. 
</P>
