<P>
EEOC Sues USAir: The U.S. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission has sued 
USAir to recover $1 million to $1.5 million in lost wages for about 300 former 
Pacific Southwest Airlines flight attendants forced to take leaves of absence 
from their jobs after the first trimester of their pregnancies. The EEOC said 
the policy was discriminatory. USAir, which acquired PSA in April, 1988, had no 
comment on the suit. 
