BOY INJURED SERIOUSLY AS HE RUNS INTO STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 5-year-old boy was seriously injured Tuesday when he was hit by a car while 
crossing the street near his Santa Ana home, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Carlos Rosas Avila was crossing the 900 block of South Standard Avenue with his 
mother about 5 p.m., when he suddenly bolted across the four-lane street. The 
boy was hit by a northbound vehicle driven by a Santa Ana man. The boy was 
dragged about 25 feet before the driver was able to bring his Datsun 200SX to a 
stop, Police Lt. Earl Porter said. 
</P>
<P>
Carlos, who suffered massive head injuries, was rushed to United Western 
Medical Center-Santa Ana, where he is was listed in serious condition, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
An investigation is under way, police said. 
